The paper deals with the computation of medians in median graphs, which are a class of graphs studied in metric graph theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper also mentions the bijections between median graphs and other structures such as CAT(0) cube complexes, domains of event structures, and solution sets of 2-SAT formulas, which are topics that fall under Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses Lexicographic Breadth First Search (LexBFS) to compute the $\Theta$-classes of a median graph, which is a data structure used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the computation of the Wiener index of a median graph, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, and cs.LG, in that order.
